text: 0:48 Ghaul is right, though. With the Traveler's Light, Guardians effectively fight like (ironically enough) gamers. We may have fought seriously for the first few years of existence, but we've probably just been going through the motions for the past century. Sure, there are darkness zones that forces us redo everything, but the fact that death isn't permanent kind off takes the edge off of everything that a Guardian does. Ghaul, on the other hand, has put his life on the line time and time again in order to prove his worth. A warrior who fights like he has everything to lose always wins, and the Light would make him effectively unstoppable. The perfect warrior. So, in a way, he really DOES deserve the Light.

text: Look at them, they come to this place when they know they are not pure. Guardians use the keys, but they are mere trespassers. Only I, Gary, know the true power of the Light. I was cut in half, destroyed, but through its Traveler, the Light called to me. It brought me here and here I was reborn. We cannot blame these creatures, they are being led by a false prophet, an impostor who knows not the secrets of the Light. Behold the Guardians, come to scavenge and desecrate this sacred realm. My brothers, did I not tell of this day? Did I not prophesize this moment? Now, I will stop them. Now I am changed, reborn through the energy of the Traveler. Forever bound to the Light. Let it be known, if the Guardians want true salvation, they will lay down their arms, and wait for the baptism of my Traveler. It is time. I will teach these trespassers the redemptive power of my Traveler. They will learn its simple truth. The Guardians are lost, and they will resist. But I, Gary, will cleanse this place of their impurity.

text: I love this game, but I'm so disappointed how bungie has punished Xbox players by not giving them the same content. This is ultimately one of the worst business practices towards customers in video games currently. No other company has had the same treatment towards customers by a third party developer, including the tomb raider deal with square enix . The PS4/Xbox console war should be fought by each respective company and not by third parties getting their pockets lined. This deal has punish players who didn't purchase a certain console and you sit in the middle and play in both markets. I've given hundreds of dollars to bungie to support an inferior product because I love this game. Shame on you bungie. I'm so disappointed in you as a developer and as a business. I'm not surprised with this decision and deal but I'm also so underwhelmed by it. I really want to support your product but I don't know if I can now out of principle.

The one thing Destiny does have is an amazing fan base that was the game for what it could become and roughed it out for a year of until we finally got a story worthwhile. Through my time playing Destiny I can count on one hand how many toxic players I have come across the people who play the game love it no matter how wonky the gun balance is or how bad the ability spam. In Destiny 2 I hope that they improve on the weak parts of the predecessor and keep the amazing fan base it has earned.

His eyes flicker weakly, his voice rumbles with overtone of vast weariness and resignation. ZAVALA (reaches up with right hand with great effort), "Ikora! It is to you, old friend, I shall pass the matrix as it was passed to me..." ANOTHER ANGLE FEATURING IKORA as she steps forward unwillingly, mixed grief and surprise on her face. IKORA, "Zavala, I'm just a scholar. I'm not worthy." ZAVALA (gasping), "Nor was I, but one day, an Guardian shall rise from our ranks and use the powers of the Matrix to *light our darkest hour*." TIGHT SHOT - IKORA AND ZAVALA  Zavala is tilted into half sitting position by other Guardians manipulating the platform as Ikora grasps his hand with great emotion . text: Already know the story. At the start, it's the same as always. You will start by picking class and customize your looks and genders. Then, a cinematic will show your character, waken up somewhere in the city. You will start to look around to see death upon the civilians and your fellow guardians. You picked up a weapon from the guardian and start to move. But, just as you were about head out and seek the others, a group of red legion cabal start heading towards you and thus surrounds you. You will end up getting really hurt from the ambush and you have no choice but to surrender. When you surrender, one of the cabal knocks you out and take you to ghaul's ship. When you wake up, you find yourself strains and couldn't move but you manage to escape somehow and begin to attempt an escape. As you try to find your way, you found yourself in empty throne room with the view of the traveler. You look at the traveler for a bit thn the huge device tht was on the traveler was activated and it covers up the whole traveler. This videos starting cinematic a goes of and ghaul kicks you off the ledge into your death. But you didn't die, you somehow survive and weak. You ended up somewhere in the city again but this time, right where the red legion is. You will have to sneak pass the red legion cabals and make your way out of the city. You escaped the city.   Thts all I have for my theories. I hope some of it will be true

text: The way I look at it, Destiny 2 is already a lot different than the 1st, whereas Destiny 1 seemed straightforward and barely any story to tell. It was all in the grimoire cards.  Now in Destiny 2, there is a story. From what we have seen, our home gets invaded. The tower destroyed, and the light taken from us. Obstacles to overcome, and something to fight for.  This is our darkest hour, and now that we are weak we have something to fear. Though since the game isn't released yet it is bit early to say whether this game will be good or bad but from everything that has been revealed to us so far, it really is a change from how the 1st Destiny started out. I'm looking forward to it.

But instead they are just hanging there awkwardly not moving, like he's extremely socially awkward. And the part where he kicks the guardian and then kicks him off the ledge looks so stupid too, because during that his fat, obese arms are just still, awkwardly hanging there. Who's fucking idea was this? Why is this Santa Claus Bane looking fuck coming in here with his stereotypical villain attitude, acting all socially awkward, only able to fight people with his feet. What, will the boss battle be him just trying to kick us with melee damage? That would be fun. And why is the titan he's talking to look SO fucking generic? His armor looks like the Pre-alpha sketches they drew. You couldn't have tried to make the guardian look unique, with cool armor? Instead just make him look the make the most boring and un-detailed as you could? Thanks for showing us a trailer for a game with 2009 graphics, in the year 2017. I really hope the actual game won't have these horrible graphics and characters can actually be detailed. But most importantly I'm looking forward to fighting a socially awkward space turtle.

text: I deleted destiny a month ago... It started when someone (i don't know who I didn't give my password to anyone) got into my account and deleted all three of my characters including wiping my vault. I never even considered cheating, and I had 1200 hours played. It happened the night after a trials card with 7 wins and a loss. Destiny was my gateway into online gaming, and it's truly a masterpiece I see now. The community can be crappy at times, but aren't all games communities? This destiny 2... the hype, the nostalgia, the support... made me realize what game I fell in love with. Thank you bungie. For reconnecting me with a lost love.
